      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "Comparison of CFD-predicted velocity fields against particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements in the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at 3500 RPM and 6 L/min. Normalized RMS error < 8% across all measurement planes.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/morrison/activity/piv-cfd-comparison-activity",
      "uofa:isFoundationalEvidence": false
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — 5-point operating map",
      "description": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by the Giersiepen power-law model embedded in the CFD solver compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. All RH values < 1.0 relative to predicate device. Mean absolute error 11.3%.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/morrison/activity/hemolysis-validation-activity",
      "uofa:isFoundationalEvidence": false
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-prior-studies-synthesis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior CFD hemolysis studies supporting model form selection",
      "description": "This result consolidates findings from more than a dozen independent published investigations of CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps conducted between 2008 and 2022. The synthesis demonstrates consistent predictive accuracy of the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law damage model across device geometries, flow regimes, and mesh resolutions, and provides the primary justification for the turbulence closure and damage-model form choices adopted in the present study. The breadth of the evidence base—spanning academic, regulatory, and industry sources—establishes strong cross-laboratory reproducibility and supports the adequacy of the model form at MRL 2.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-hemolysis-claim"
    }
  ],
  "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4043479",
